# Exercise Profile

## Mobility & Physical Condition
- **Condition:** Osteoarthritis (knee soreness).
- **Mobility Level:** 
    - Prefers seated exercises.
    - Good upper body strength.
    - Can stand for short periods with support.
- **Pain Triggers:** Leg extensions (causes knee pain); rapid movements; standing longer than 2 minutes.

## Exercise Preferences
- **Preferred:** Neck rolls, shoulder work, arm circles, stretches, seated marching (if knees permit), deep breathing, and relaxation.
- **Avoid:** High-impact movements, leg extensions, standing > 2 mins, rapid movements.

## Schedule & History
- **Target Schedule:** Daily, ideally 10:00 AM for 15-20 minutes.
- **Recent Activity:** Set alarm for 1:00 PM exercise session on 2026-05-13.
- **Recent Pain Report:** Reported knee soreness on 2026-05-13.